will accept and support negative boosting.  Is that the case?

Regards,

Terry

  ----- Original Message -----=20
  From: Erik Hatcher=20
  To: Lucene Users List=20
  Sent: Wednesday, August 04, 2004 9:12 AM
  Subject: Re: Negative Boost


  On Aug 4, 2004, at 7:19 AM, Terry Steichen wrote:
  > I can't get negative boosts to work with QueryParser.  Is it =
possible=20
  > to do so?

  Closer inspection on the parsing:

  <Boost> TOKEN : {
  <NUMBER:    (<_NUM_CHAR>)+ ( "." (<_NUM_CHAR>)+ )? > : DEFAULT
  }

  where

     <#_NUM_CHAR:   ["0"-"9"] >

  So, no, negative boosts don't appear possible with QueryParser=20
  currently.  I have no objections if you'd like to enhance the grammar=20
  to allow for it (provided sufficient unit tests, of course).

  Erik


