On Friday 06 August 2004 08:37, Tino Sch=F6llhorn wrote:

> I am aware that the Lucene Query-Api supports wildcards, but as far as I
> know I cannot add a * in front of a query-term.

That should be possible, but it will be slow if you have many terms. Anothe=
r=20
idea is to additionally index the word in reverse order: bergbahn ->=20
nhabgreb, then a query for nhab* will find all words that end with bahn (yo=
u=20
can use a prefix query then, which is not as slow as a WildcardQuery but=20
still slow).

Regards
 Daniel


