Mime-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=ISO-8859-1
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit
X-Mailer: Treklogic MailTool v1.6 http://www.treklogic.com
X-Virus-Checked: Checked
X-Spam-Rating: minotaur-2.apache.org 1.6.2 0/1000/N

This is how I do it:

IndexSearcher[] is = new IndexSearcher[2];

is[0] = new IndexSearcher(IndexDir1); // first index folder
is[1] = new IndexSearcher(IndexDir2); // second index folder

MultiSearcher searcher = new MultiSearcher(is);

searcher.search(query);

I think that the MulitSearcher is only doing sequential search. Alternately, you can use ParallelMultiSearcher which allows you to do the search in parallel.

Hope this helps,
Terence



> FYI
>  
