X-Virus-Checked: Checked
X-Spam-Rating: minotaur-2.apache.org 1.6.2 0/1000/N

Hi Santosh,

Lucene doesn't search pdfs per se.  To make anything searchable you have =
to first extract the content and then put it in lucene in a form it =
understands (i.e document objects).  So in order to search your pdfs you =
first need to extract the info from the PDFs using something like =
PDFBox.  So your battleplan should be forget lucene for a while, get the =
raw data out of all the items you want to search. Then look at the =
lucene articles about creating simple searchable indices.

DT

"If we didn't train to fight, who'd fight the wars?" :)

