I could ber wrong, but I don't think that there is an indexer for word
documents.<br>
<br>
There's a Python version of Lucene called Lupy with a Python indexer
for all sorts of document types
(<a class="moz-txt-link-freetext" href="http://www.methods.co.nz/docindexer/">http://www.methods.co.nz/docindexer/</a>).&nbsp; Would anyone be willing to
port those over.&nbsp; Although the MSWord indexer only words on MSWindows
and you may need MSWord for it to work.&nbsp; Man, that's no good.<br>
<br>
I think that we'd need to ask the OpenOffice people for help on this.<br>
<br>
