hi,

in general the query parser doesn't allow queries which start with a=20
wildcard Those queries could end up with very long response times and=20
block your system. This is not what you want.

I'm not sure if i understand what you want to do. I expect that you have

a field within a lucene document with name "type". For this field you=20
can have different values like "contact,account" etc. Now you want to=20
search all documents where type is "contact". So the query to do this=20
would be "type:contact", nothing else is required.

can you try that and give some feedback ?

best regards
Bernhard


